Well......I have not updated properly in a while, cause I had exams and all I was doing was preparing for them. So yeah now that I have finished I will let you know what has been happening.

My sister had her baby, a little baby boy named Decklan, soooo cute. He is about 6 weeks old now and is really well behaved apparentley. Katie finally got her license so she is able to go around with the baby and stuff as she has a car.

Speaking of cars mine is in the mechanics today to see what exactly is wrong with it. The mechanica next door seem to think that the head is gone but I decided to take it back to the mechanics that have looked after the car most of its life. So yeah they are going to do a written report and let us know how bad it really is. If it is too much repairs needed then I am going to get a new car. Well not nex but second hand and yeah newer then the current one. I dont know what I want yet, so I will decide when I need to.

We went to the red bull air race on Sunday. I got a little burnt (like a lobster), even though I used sunscreen and was under cover most of the day. GRRRRRRRRRRR. It is not as sore as when we went to cervanties. Honestly the air race was not that good (could not see half of it but yeah) didnt seem that interesting. But I did enjoy watching one of the australian jets do a display it was awesome. I broke the sound barrier in front of us and you could see the slip stream and everything. It was awesome.

About Cervanties, We had fun GO THE EAGLES!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! We went and saw the pinacles aswell which was good. Got burnt to a crisp there as the sand reflects aswell so yeah not good man. The weekend was good and going along the beach in cols new car was fun as. 

Yeah about Colin, thats about all he gets in my LJ because I never made it into his :P. So ner!!!!

Anyways should actually do some work.

Bye Bye

Im back at uni now...... I dont know if this is a good thing but yeah i'll find out soon. I am doing management, finance, economics and also information systems. I have to say that so far my fave lectures this semester are my management and information systems ones. I am yet to meet the finance one so tonight I shall know if I like them or not. In other news my sister is getting fatter and fatter and it was really good to go to her mock baby shower the other week. The reason I say mock was that it was only because her best friend kelly was going back to ireland for about 2 months and incase she was not back before kt had the baby she wanted kelly to be there. Yeah I am so in love with colin at the moment. I dont know why I just love him heaps. Even though he has been rejecting me to play world of warcraft of late (:P he does not reject me I just take what attention I want behehehe). Been playing lots and lots of outdoor tag as we have got the new and inproved guns which are more then heaps of fun. It's good to play against people who are getting quite good at the outdoor scene. The best bit is that it is really building strong friendships with the darklight leagues. We play agianst and fight it all out on wednesday nights in the arena but because we are hanging and enjoying the outdoor games in between games there is a lot more fun. People (except for a few unsaid pains) feel more like they can walk up and chat to whoever. But saying that wednesdays are coming a bit harder when you have team captains who are 32 acting like 2 yr olds. Its just a bit like stupid. If your team aint there on time then tough the game starts without you. But yeah im over it now. :P. Anyways I might go to the shops now and get something to eat and also get my passport photo done (for my new bank account hehehehehe it's cool when you get student ID with a bank account).

So first things first! I passed all my units at uni YAY! It is soo good to have that pressure off of my back. I was really stressing about it. I didnt do as well as I thought I would but you get that I still passed ok. I am going to really work hard at it next semester and make sure that I have no doubt that I pass. I got two Passes, a credit and a Distinction. The distinction I got in my proffesional Communication class which is not a surprise cause like it was all about talking and giving speeches and well I could talk forever it runs on the family. 

Another thing cograts to Jody on getting engaged. And also for making your 1 year. It makes me think I have lost count how long Colin and I have been going out for. I mean I can sit there and work it out and what not but like I cant think about it straight away I have to work it out. But yeah we have been going out for over 14 months now and I dont see us stopping anytime soon. It really is nice to know that there is still atleast one decent man around in the world still. Cause he is you know. He does not treat me like shit. He looks after me when I need looking after. And the one thing that I like him for the most is that if I seriously sat down with him and wanted to talk about things he would sit there and listen and be the best pillar of support I can have. He really is a decent man and I feel privliged everyday to know that I cuddle him at night no-one else. The best bit is that I fall in love with him over and over again everyday. He makes me smile all the time and I am quite happy that I have found myself a great guy. Its funny to think that I met him on the Internet. See internet romances do work. And well the sex is bloody first class so I am not complaining on any part.

In other news my sister is like blown up like a balloon at the moment. She looks sooo cute with her big tummy and stuff. Pitty she is still a bitch. LOL!!

As far as Colin and I go. Everything is all good and peachy (I dont know where that came in it just sounded good at the time ok). I absolutley love him to death and he is my baby OK.
